description: Smallest number that begins with 1, has digits in order 123...901... and is divisible by n. If no such number exists then a(n) = 0.
crossrefs: Cf. A061805. Length of n-th term gives A061311.
author: _Amarnath Murthy_, May 28 2001
extensions: Corrected and extended by _Frank Ellermann_, May 28 2001.
